news.title: Mumbai: Chembur society repays Rs 20 crore loan six months after OC
news.para: Chitra is one among several societies in Mumbai which did not reach out to private builders and instead opted to redevelop their buildings themselves by appointing consultants, architects and contractors.

news.title: Greater Noida authority cracks down on illegal construction to reclaim land worth Rs 150 crore
news.para: On Saturday morning, a team from Work Circle Three demolished ongoing illegal constructions on plots numbered 517, 964, 981, 985, 995 and 1,007 in Tusyana village," the statement said.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC directs Chandigarh administration to finish construction of flats within two months
news.para: A division bench, comprising Justice Sureshwar Thakur and Justice Lalit Batra, directed, “A mandamus is also passed, upon the Board (Chandigarh Housing Board) to ensure that encumbrance free delivery of possession of flats is made to the petitioners.

news.title: Real estate sector pushes for tax rationalization and reduced approval cost
news.para: With Narendra Modi set to take oath as Prime Minister for the third time, the real estate industry has high expectations from Modi 3.0. The interim budget announced a boost for affordable housing by adding 2 crore more houses to the PMAY-U scheme.

news.title: SC stays Telangana HC order on 74 acre land parcel in Kukatpally
news.para: According to an order pronounced by a single judge of high court on March 31, 2023, Pilli Balaiah and five others were cultivating the land from 1962 and purchased 81 acres from land owner Mir Fazeelath Hussain on April 4, 1974, through an unregistered sale deed.

news.title: Raymond to redevelop MIG VI CHS society in Mumbai
news.para: Spread across two acres, the project and has a revenue potential of over Rs 2,000 crore over the project period.

news.title: Land prices soar in Amaravati
news.para: Land prices came down anywhere between 60% and 75% after outgoing chief minister Y S Jagan Mohan Reddy announced his plans of three capitals in 2019.

news.title: About 14 of 38 projects under AMRUT scheme on track
news.para: The projects include the rejuvenation of waterbodies at 21 locations, revamping of green spaces at five sites, and the implementation of sewerage management projects at 12 locations by the engineering department.

news.title: Two hotels in Kochi closed for release of untreated waste into canal
news.para: The illegal activity came to the health wing’s attention after a vigilant resident on Thursday captured the visuals of hotels discharging untreated waste directly into the canal in broad daylight on his mobile phone.

news.title: Bihar RERA refunded Rs 14 lakh to homebuyers
news.para: ​A sum of Rs 14.23 lakh was recently refunded by an erring promoter to two homebuyers in the cases which were transferred to the Patna district administration for recovery of amount under relevant provisions of the Bihar and Orissa Public Demand Recovery Act (PDRA), 1914.

news.title: Home buyers concerned about corruption in sub registrar offices in Bengaluru
news.para: Amidst complaints and pending grievances, authorities issue notices but actions remain elusive, leaving home buyers vulnerable to fraudulent practices.

news.title: Why outage-hit societies in Greater Noida West will have to look within for relief
news.para: The discom has asked the society maintenance teams to augment their infrastructure at the earliest and has handed out manuals for guidance in electrical equipment upkeep as well.

news.title: Gurugram: Officers told to monitor work on substation as Vatika India Next township faces outages
news.para: Expressing frustration and distress due to the persisting outages, locals said that despite eight years of occupancy as well as repeated complaints, the developer has failed to set up the 33kV substation.

news.title: Tripti Dimri buys bungalow in Mumbai's Bandra West for over Rs 14 crore
news.para: The bungalow, house number 25 on Sherly Rajan Road, has a total land area of 2,226 square feet, and the house spanning across the ground floor and two additional levels has a total built up area of 2,194 sq ft.

news.title: Stuck since 2011, YEIDA to register 800 plots if buyers pay for farmers' aid
news.para: The 800-odd buyers have also been asked to get an NOC from the builder — SDS Infracon — which they say is the bone of contention.

news.title: Delhi court grants bail to Unitech directors in money laundering case
news.para: ​According to the Enforcement Directorate, the accused, along with others, collected funds running into several hundred crores from the home buyers for housing projects.

news.title: Will engage with IRP of Jaiprakash Associates on cement asset acquisition: Dalmia Bharat
news.para: ​The company, which had announced acquisition of the cement almost 18 month back, however, it still remains incomplete, because of the ongoing discussion between JAL's lenders and an arbitration with UltraTech.
